What does a doctype do?
-	Doctype is found at the top of all documents
-	Prevent a browser from switching into “quirk mode” when rendering a document
-	Instructs the browser to render the page 
-	First thing that needs to be done in text editor, so in atom, it would be html tab

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title></title>
  </head>
  <body>
    
  </body>
</html>


How do you serve a page with content in multiple languages?
-	UTF8 is a good way to display content in multiple languages 
-	For a user to specify the language:
o	Use the accept language header 
o	In the lang tag in html doctype – it is specified 
-	For server side frameworks and CMS (content management system):
o	i18n modules  these support multi language content and for the client side there are i18n language selectors to change between translations 
o	i18n is the process of preparing software so that it can support local languages 
o	stored in yml and json formats
	Definition: YML
•	Uses a text file and organizes it into a format which is human readable 


What kind of things must you be wary of when design or developing for multilingual sites?

-	Use utf-8 bc it helps support many languages
-	Use a lang attribute in html head 
-	Allow a user to change languages easily without hassle 
-	Avoid designs where amount of text could make or break a design as content can be shorter / longer in other languages 
-	Be mindful of how colors are perceived 
-	Formatting dates and currencies and language syntax correctly for other languages 
-	Use template strings w/ parameters substitutions for each language instead of concatenated strings bc that will break 
-	Acknowledge some languages don’t read left to right and top to bottom so give it a language reading direction 


